HURST (Pros. Atty.) vs. WARNER (J. of P.), No. 13974, 102 M., 238.

(Certiorari to Chippewa.)

To compel respondent to issue a warrant .for the violation of a rule adopted by the State Board of Health under Act No. 17, *228Laws of 1893, relative to the disinfection of baggage coming from infected localities.

Denied September 27, 1894.

Held, that the rule was not warranted by the statute.
